1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper investigates the diversity order of MMSE-based optimal transceivers in MIMO AF relaying systems, which is a topic closely related to information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with MIMO AF relaying systems, which are commonly used in wireless networks, and investigates the performance of MMSE transceivers, which are important components of wireless communication systems.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the performance of a system (MIMO AF relaying system) with a specific type of transceiver (MMSE), which falls under the scope of systems and control.
4. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - This category is less likely, but the paper may have some implications for the design and optimization of wireless communication systems, which can have social and economic impacts.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - This category is also less likely, but the paper may have some relevance to multimedia applications that rely on wireless communication systems, such as video streaming or online gaming.
